			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Digital Marketing Intern</strong></p>
<p>
Penango, Inc. is looking for an enthusiastic marketing intern to help us coordinate and execute our digital marketing efforts across many channels. You will work closely with our senior staff and experienced advisors to get the word out about Penango&rsquo;s approach to and implementation of end-to-end authentication and encryption on the Internet. Join our vibrant team and make history!</p>
<p>
<strong>Essential Duties and Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Work with our Chief Marketing Officer&nbsp;and the rest of the team to implement our marketing strategies on channels including Google Search, Google Adwords, app stores, other search engines, Internet advertising channels, and social media (LinkedIn, Twitter, Facebook, etc.)</li>
<li>
Improve our site&rsquo;s SEO for additional measured lead generation</li>
<li>
Track usage of site and prospects via marketing campaigns</li>
<li>
Improve our e-mail marketing channel</li>
<li>
Assist with collateral and other materials during the sales process</li>
<li>
Be an analytical thinker</li>
<li>
Generate more mentions of Penango in online media outlets</li>
<li>
Help brainstorm new marketing strategies, including digital video outreach (YouTube)</li>
<li>
Maintain up-to-date knowledge necessary to respond to customer needs using trade journals, the Internet, forums, and other sources</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent work experience in digital media marketing</li>
<li>
SEO experience</li>
<li>
Track record of success and enthusiasm</li>
<li>
Can write about technical topics with ease and fluency, communicating complex ideas to audiences in easy-to-understand ways</li>
<li>
Must have excellent problem-solving skills to understand our customers and provide relevant content for their needs</li>
<li>
Must be able to work in West Los Angeles, CA at least three days per week (parking available)</li>
<li>
Must have work authorization in the US</li>
<li>
Multi-platform experience a plus</li>
<li>
Familiarity with marketing to enterprise, government, and military customers a plus</li>
</ul>
<p>
The internship includes a monthly stipend. Follow-on full-time hiring is possible. If you&rsquo;re looking for a great opportunity with a growing company, come to Penango.</p>
<p>
<strong>About Penango</strong></p>
<p>
Penango is dedicated to improving the security and experience of online communications for enterprises, governments, and end users all over the world. Our first product, the Penango Webmail Client, enables end-to-end secure messaging in common webmail environments such as Gmail and Google Apps. Penango&rsquo;s solution meets the strictest government and military standards for e-mail security, and as a result Penango is used by actual militaries and government offices to protect their valuable and sensitive information.</p>
